==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
Neuter of a derivative from an inseparable prefix akin to [[ἅμα]] {{GG|260}} (through the idea of partition involved in connection) and meaning semi-; 

===Pronunciation===
*ἥμισυ / hēmisu / hay'-mee-soo

===Noun===
'''ἥμισυ'''

# (as noun) half: - [[half]].

